'!' marks the creation of a variable
- '!user' 
  creates a variable with the name of user

'->' is how you assign values to variables
- '!user -> nesboldt'
  gives the variable 'user' the value of 'nesboldt'

'?' is how you print to the console
- '?'nesboldt'' 
  will print 'nesboldt' to the console

'~' is how you create a function (use {} for functions)
- '~greet{
     ?'hello'
} 
greet()
- will create a function named greet, that, when called, will print 'hello' to the console

you can also just have functions return values
~greet{
return 'hello'
}
?greet()
- will print 'hello' to the console

'##' is how you signify comments
- ##this will do nothing
  will do nothing but give you a reminder about what a certain line of code does, etc. 

